\]margin error critical value multiplied standard error, right side expression. equations, \(\sqrt{n}\) denominator standard error. Suppose calculate confidence interval based sample size 100. , confidence interval based sample size 200 standard error reduced factor \(1/\sqrt{2}\). Compared original interval (sample size 100), confidence interval based sample size 400 standard error reduced factor \(1/\sqrt{4} = 1/2\). sample size increases, standard error (hence, margin error) decreases, interval gets narrow. can think another way: sample size increases gain information population, confidence interval gets precise. smaller sample size (less information population) results wider confidence interval.

